==English==

===Verb phrase===
'''[[tuck]] [[in]]'''

#{{idiom}} {{transitive}} To pull the [[blankets]] or [[duvet]] up over (somebody in bed); to put (somebody) to [[bed]].
#:''She '''tucked in''' her young son and turned out the light.''
#{{idiom}} {{intransitive}} To start to eat.
#:''Tuck in, before the food goes cold.''

